My road is a long road which leads off the main Frimley Road, but the end part is surprisingly quiet, not only is it a cul-de-sac, but there are only houses along one side, the other side being fields and woodland of the {Blackwater Valley.}
The river is slow and meandering, and the valley is so shallow I didn't know there was one until I researched this project.
This area would probably have been dense marsh land when the original Domesday Book was written in 1085. The fertility of the marsh land still lingers on and this is why there are large numbers of allotments in this area.
